# UI Design Rules for AI Implementation

1. Color Harmony and Accessibility
   - Use a consistent color palette with 2-3 primary colors and 2-3 accent colors
   - Ensure sufficient color contrast (WCAG 2.1 standards)
   - Include dark/light mode support
   - Use color psychology principles for emotional impact
   - Provide colorblind-friendly alternatives

2. Typography Hierarchy 
   - Limit to 2-3 font families maximum
   - Maintain consistent font sizes and weights
   - Use clear heading hierarchy (H1, H2, H3)
   - Ensure readable line lengths (50-75 characters)
   - Set appropriate line height (1.5-1.6 for body text)

3. Layout and Spacing
   - Follow a consistent grid system
   - Use whitespace effectively
   - Maintain balanced visual hierarchy
   - Keep layouts responsive and adaptive
   - Apply consistent padding and margins
   - Use the 8pt grid system

4. Interactive Elements
   - Clear hover/active states
   - Consistent button styles
   - Obvious clickable elements
   - Touch targets minimum 44x44px
   - Loading states and feedback
   - Smooth transitions (200-300ms)

5. Visual Feedback
   - Clear success/error states
   - Progress indicators
   - Micro-interactions
   - Subtle animations (max 400ms)
   - System status visibility
   - Confirmation messages

6. Navigation and Information Architecture
   - Clear navigation hierarchy
   - Breadcrumb trails where needed
   - Search functionality
   - Back buttons where appropriate
   - Consistent menu placement
   - Maximum 3 clicks to content

7. Content Presentation
   - Scannable content blocks
   - Clear section headers
   - Bulleted lists for multiple items
   - Appropriate image sizing
   - Loading optimization
   - Placeholder states

8. Form Design
   - Clear input labels
   - Visible validation rules
   - Error prevention
   - Required field indicators
   - Logical tab order
   - Auto-focus on first field

9. Responsive Design
   - Mobile-first approach
   - Flexible layouts
   - Breakpoint consistency
   - Touch-friendly interfaces
   - Content prioritization
   - Performance optimization

10. Accessibility Features
    - ARIA labels
    - Keyboard navigation
    - Screen reader support
    - Focus indicators
    - Alt text for images
    - Skip navigation links

11. Brand Consistency
    - Logo placement rules
    - Brand color usage
    - Typography guidelines
    - Icon style consistency
    - Voice and tone
    - Visual language

12. Performance Guidelines
    - Image optimization
    - Lazy loading
    - Caching strategies
    - Minimal HTTP requests
    - Code optimization
    - Resource prioritization
